06:28.880 --> 06:31.280
So which aspects do you find convincing?

06:31.280 --> 06:34.400
Can you steelman that case and then can you argue against it?

06:35.040 --> 06:41.840
So what aspects I find convincing is that human finitude, being finite,

06:42.560 --> 06:46.720
being inherently limited is very problematic for us.

06:49.360 --> 06:54.000
Given the extensive use of the word problematic, I like that you use that word

06:54.000 --> 06:57.200
to describe one's own mortality as problematic.

06:57.200 --> 07:01.760
Because people sort of on Twitter use the word problematic when they disagree with somebody.

07:01.760 --> 07:06.320
But this to me seems to be the ultimate problematic aspect of the human condition

07:06.320 --> 07:08.480
is that we die and it ends.

07:08.480 --> 07:14.320
I think I'm not just agreeing with you, but I'm trying to get you to consider

07:14.320 --> 07:16.800
that your mortality is not an event in the future.

07:16.800 --> 07:18.240
It's a state you're in right now.

07:19.360 --> 07:22.000
That's what I'm trying to shift.

07:23.360 --> 07:29.120
So your mortality is just a, we talk about something that causes mortality fatal.

07:30.160 --> 07:33.440
But what we actually mean is it's full of fate.

