09:01.680 --> 09:05.920
a self-report on a survey is not an accurate way to capture what is actually

09:06.000 --> 09:10.640
at the core of the motivation of a human being, that we could be terrified of death.

09:10.640 --> 09:18.480
And from childhood, since we realized the absurdity of the fact that the right ends,

09:18.480 --> 09:22.400
we've learned to really try to forget about it.

09:22.400 --> 09:28.000
Try to construct illusions that allow us to escape momentarily

09:28.000 --> 09:32.080
over prolonged periods of time the realization that we die.

09:32.400 --> 09:37.840
So first, I took it seriously, but now I want to say why there's some empirical work

09:37.840 --> 09:39.680
that makes me want to reconsider.

09:39.680 --> 09:45.680
So terror management theory is you do things like you give people a list of words to read,

09:45.680 --> 09:50.880
and in those words, in those lists are words associated with death, cough and funeral.

09:50.880 --> 09:52.560
And then you see what happens to people.

09:52.560 --> 09:55.600
And generally, they start to become more rigid in their thinking.

09:55.600 --> 09:57.600
They tend to identify with their worldview.

09:58.800 --> 10:00.320
They lose cognitive flexibility.

10:00.560 --> 10:03.440
That's if you present it to them in that third person perspective.

10:03.440 --> 10:09.040
But if you get them to go in the first person perspective and imagine that they're dying

10:09.600 --> 10:16.320
and that the people that they care about are there with them, they don't show those responses.

10:16.320 --> 10:21.760
In fact, they show us an increase in cognitive flexibility, an increase in openness.

10:21.760 --> 10:25.840
See, so I'm trying to say we might be putting the cart before the horse.

10:25.840 --> 10:30.160
The cart before the horse, it might not be death per se, but the kind of meaning that

10:30.160 --> 10:32.400
is present or absent in depth.

10:32.400 --> 10:33.840
That is the crucial thing for us.

10:34.560 --> 10:37.360
By the way, to push back, I don't think you took it seriously.

10:37.360 --> 10:43.120
I don't think you truly steelman the case because you're saying that death is always

10:43.120 --> 10:43.920
present with us.

