Are you personally afraid of your death?

11:38.400 --> 11:39.760
Do you think about it?

11:39.760 --> 11:46.000
As somebody who produces a lot of ideas, records them, writes them down,

11:46.800 --> 11:52.400
is a deep thinker, admired thinker, and as the years go on, become more and more admired.

11:53.600 --> 11:56.400
Does it scare you that the ride ends?

11:58.080 --> 12:00.480
No, I mean, you have to talk to me on all my levels.

12:00.480 --> 12:05.120
I'm a biological organism, so something's thrown at my head all duck and things like that.

12:05.920 --> 12:10.880
But if you're asking me, do I long to live forever?

12:11.760 --> 12:12.080
No.

12:13.040 --> 12:16.880
In the Buddhist tradition, there are practices that are designed to make you

12:17.440 --> 12:21.920
aware of simultaneously the horror of mortality and the horror of immortality.

12:22.640 --> 12:27.280
The thought of living forever is actually horrific to me.

12:29.040 --> 12:30.400
Are those the only two options?

12:34.080 --> 12:40.800
